Scripture
Purpose: Holds the scripture text and manages hiding words.
Responsibilities:

Store the reference

Store a list of Word objects

Hide random words

Check if all words are hidden

Display the scripture with hidden words replaced

Code
-----------------------------------------
|               Scripture                |
-----------------------------------------
| - _reference : ScriptureReference      |
| - _words : List<Word>                  |
| - _rng : Random                        |
-----------------------------------------
| + Scripture(reference, text)           |
| + HideRandomWords(count)               |
| + IsFullyHidden() : bool               |
| + GetDisplayText() : string            |
-----------------------------------------





Program Flow Description

1. Load Scripture
Program creates a ScriptureReference object

Program creates a Scripture object using the reference and full text

Scripture splits the text into Word objects

2. Display Scripture
Program calls scripture.GetDisplayText()

Words that are hidden show as "_____"

Visible words show normally

3. Loop Until User Quits or All Words Hidden
Program waits for user input

Press Enter hide a few random words

Type “quit” exit

Program calls scripture.HideRandomWords()

Program redisplays the scripture

Program checks scripture.IsFullyHidden()

If true end program

4. End Program

When all words are hidden or user quits, program exits